@startuml shell-integration-activity
' Activity diagram: shell-integration entry point through to user
' confirmation. Nice-to-have per the audit (priority: nice-to-have).
'
' Conveys: how a user reaches aiobi-term without typing the full command
' by hand — either via the readline Ctrl-X Ctrl-A binding (shell-scoped,
' works everywhere bash reads input) or via bash-completion (TAB-driven,
' argument-scoped) — and what happens after aiobi-term returns a
' suggestion: the destructive-pattern guardrail gates on user
' confirmation before anything is ever run, and aiobi-term itself never
' executes the suggestion on the user's behalf.
'
' Source read: Engineering log material on script 21 (readline binds:
' TAB = menu-complete, Shift+Tab, show-all-if-ambiguous,
' menu-complete-display-prefix) + aiobi-term do_command()/is_destructive().
'
' Canonical reference: Figure 4.13 — Shell-Integration Activity (nice-to-have)

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam titleFontColor #7233CD
skinparam activity {
  BorderColor #4A3C5C
  BackgroundColor #F8F8F9
  ArrowColor #7233CD
  DiamondBorderColor #4A3C5C
  DiamondBackgroundColor #F8F8F9
}

title Shell integration — from keystroke to (optional) execution

start
:user typing at the bash prompt;

if (entry point?) then (readline bind\nCtrl-X Ctrl-A)
  :readline invokes aiobi-term\non the current line buffer;
else (TAB-driven\nbash-completion)
  :bash-completion offers\nmenu-complete on TAB,\nShift+Tab cycles backward;
  :user selects a completion\nor lets it fall through\nto aiobi-term --cmd;
endif

:aiobi-term --cmd "<request>"\n(see Figure 4.11 for the full round trip);

if (destructive pattern detected?) then (yes)
  :prepend\n"# WARNING: destructive pattern\ndetected (<reason>)."\nto the printed suggestion;
else (no)
endif

:print suggestion to stdout\n(never executed automatically);

if (user reviews and decides) then (run it)
  :user manually pastes / confirms\nthe command at the prompt;
  :shell executes\n(outside aiobi-term's control);
else (discard)
  :user ignores the suggestion;
endif

stop

@enduml
